When Cunningham wanted to sell his house in 2003, he didn't bother to put it on the market. MZM, one of Cunningham's top campaign donors, obtained millions in government contracts; the congressman, who also sits on the House intelligence committee, acknowledged to Stern that he had helped MZM win contracts, as he said he has helped other firms. Instead, according to reporting by Marcus Stern of Copley News Service, Cunningham -- who sits on the defense appropriations subcommittee -- turned to a defense contractor. 